<header>
<div id="instruction">
	Look at the following statements about the speaking test and decide whether they are true or false.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set10_02.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <div id="content1">
  <ol>
    <li id="q1">You will have to talk about yourself.</li>
		<a id="a1"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a2"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q2">The Examiner will ask you to call him or her Mr / Ms X.</li>
		<a id="a3"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a4"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q3">You need to have a lot of information about a lot of topics.</li>
		<a id="a5"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a6"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q4">The Examiner will ask all the questions.</li>
		<a id="a7"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a8"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q5">The interview time will vary a little from candidate to candidate.</li>
		<a id="a9"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a10"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q6">You can ask about your marks.</li>
		<a id="a11"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a12"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q7">The Examiner may judge you partly on your appearance.</li>
		<a id="a13"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a14"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q8">The Examiner will ask where you are from.</li>
		<a id="a15"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a16"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q9">Giving examples to support your opinion will help you do better.</li>
		<a id="a17"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a18"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q10">The discussion topic will be chosen by the Examiner.</li>
		<a id="a19"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a20"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q11">You are required to have definite opinions.</li>
		<a id="a21"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a22"><b>False</b></a>
    <p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q12">You must communicate, no matter what topic is presented.</li>
		<a id="a23"><b>True</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a24"><b>False</b></a>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
  </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    1. You will probably be asked about what you do and where you are from.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    2. Examiners will give you their full name and will not ask you to call them anything.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    3. This test is about communication not knowledge. 
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    4. You can ask examiners to repeat a question but you shouldn't ask them anything else.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    5. The test is between 11 and 14 minutes.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    6. You will find out how well you did when you get your test results, no sooner!
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    7. Looking nice helps with the impression you give but the examiner is there to mark your communication.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    8. It is a good idea to give some extra information as the examiner may not know your country very well.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    9. Giving examples and explanations is always a good idea.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    10. Examiners have several topics to choose from.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb11">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    11. You are only expected to communicate your thoughts, not have definite opinions. 
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb12">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    12. You should do your best with whichever topic you get.
  </p>
</section>

